Notes on Collection and Biology.
Most individuals were collected from the twilight to dark zone of Huangu Cave (
Figs. 2A–C
) and Mengjia Cave (
Figs. 2D–F
), typically in areas 
10–50 m
from the entrance. A majority of the adults were found under stones (
Figs. 2G, H
), while a few were spotted wandering around on cave walls. A single male was collected under a stone from the twilight zone of Shenxian Cave, about 
10 m
from the entrance.
